The corpse of a two-week-old baby is among 30 unclaimed corpses at the Asokoro District Hospital, Abuja. The hospital’s management in a publication yesterday, said it would dispose the corpses if not claimed in seven days. “Interested persons are free to visit the Asokoro District Hospital morgue for possible identification,” it said. The corpse of the baby was deposited at the morgue in October, 2018. 18 other corpses were also taken to the hospital’s morgue same year, while 11 were deposited in 2019.  Unclaimed corpses, sharp practices stifle Abuja mortuaries 4 mortuary attendants docked over disappearance of day-old baby’s corpse Maitama hospital to bury 26 abandoned corpses Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin